          </ul></div><div id="posts"><article class="post type-text" id=""><aside class="metadata "></aside><h2><a href="all">All Lessons</a></h2><div class="caption clearfix rte"><p>So here we are, here&rsquo;s a list of all the lessons we&rsquo;ve ever posted on the site! If you&rsquo;re looking to learn Hindi from a complete beginner&rsquo;s level then check out <a href="intro">Introduction Section</a>. Oh and this list sure is pretty long, don&rsquo;t get lost!</p><h3><a href="post/706242869/into-1-about-hindi">Intro #1: About Hindi</a></h3><h3><a href="post/706309376/intro-2-some-helpful-ideas">Intro #2: Some Helpful Ideas</a></h3><h3><a href="post/1021543673/intro-3-devanagari-the-hindi-alphabet">Intro #3: Devanagari - The Hindi Alphabet</a></h3><h3><a href="post/2168028712/intro-4-an-introduction-to-urdu">Intro #4: An Introduction to Urdu - &#1575;&#1585;&#1583;&#1608;</a></h3><h3><a href="post/716551335/lesson-1-hello">Lesson #1: Saying Hello</a></h3><h3><a href="post/727352299/lesson-2-vowels-part-1-and">Lesson #2: Vowels part 1; &#2309; <em>a</em> and &#2310; <em>aa</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/732878148/lesson-3-vowels-part-2-and">Lesson #3: Vowels part 2; &#2311;<em> i</em> and &#2312; <em>ee</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/743955682/lesson-5-vowels-part-4-and">Lesson #4: Vowels part 3; &#2313; <em>u</em> and &#2314; <em>oo</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/740061542/lesson-4-vowels-part-3-and">Lesson #5: Vowels part 4; &#2319; <em>e</em> and &#2320; <em>ai</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/755506737/lesson-6-vowels-part-5-and">Lesson #6: Vowels part 5; &#2323; <em>o</em> and &#2324; <em>au</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/773880849/lesson-7-vowels-part-6">Lesson #7: Vowels part 6; &#2315; <em>ri</em></a></h3><h3><a href="post/781709399/lesson-8-vowels-recap">Lesson #8: Vowels Recap</a></h3><h3><a href="post/798066644/lesson-9-consonants-part-1-and">Lesson #9: Consonants part 1; &#2325;, &#2326;, &#2327; and &#2328;</a></h3><h3><a href="post/798923563/lesson-10-how-to-type-in-hindi">Lesson #10: How to Type in Hindi</a></h3><h3><a href="post/804557021/lesson-11-consonants-part-2-and">Lesson #11: Consonants part 2; &#2330;, &#2331;, &#2332; and &#2333;</a></h3><h3><a href="post/809126458/lesson-12-numbers-0-10">Lesson #12: Numbers 0 - 10</a></h3><h3><a href="post/821127618/lesson-13-consonants-part-3-and">Lesson #13: Consonants part 3; &#2335;, &#2336;, &#2337; and &#2338;</a></h3><h3><a href="post/842512665/lesson-14-consonants-part-4-and">Lesson #14: Consonants part 4; &#2340;, &#2341;, &#2342; and &#2343;</a></h3><h3><a href="post/853847321/lesson-15-pronouns">Lesson #15: Pronouns</a></h3><h3><a href="post/858244745/lesson-16-consonants-part-5-and">Lesson #16: Consonants part 5; &#2346;, &#2347;, &#2348;, &#2349; and &#2350;</a></h3><h3><a href="post/862964443/lesson-17-how-are-you">Lesson #17: How are You?</a></h3><h3><a href="post/871458843/lesson-18-consonants-part-6-and">Lesson #18: Consonants part 6; &#2351;, &#2352;, &#2354; and &#2357;</a></h3><h3><a href="post/880500641/lesson-19-numbers-11-20">Lesson #19: Numbers 11 - 20</a></h3><h3><a href="post/889680515/lesson-20-what-is-your-name">Lesson #20: What is your name?</a></h3><h3><a href="post/895217882/lesson-21-handwriting">Lesson #21: Handwriting</a></h3><h3><a href="post/899032290/lesson-22-to-be">Lesson #22: &#2361;&#2379;&#2344;&#2366; - To Be</a></h3><h3><a href="post/908470587/lesson-23-consonants-part-7-and">Lesson #23: Consonants part 7; &#2358;, &#2359;, &#2360; and &#2361;</a></h3><h3><a href="post/913325626/lesson-24-correction-on-and">Lesson #24: Nasalised Vowels</a></h3><h3><a href="post/918920151/lesson-25-verbs-part-1">Lesson #25: Introduction to Hindi Verbs</a></h3><h3><a href="post/928456073/lesson-26-yes-no-and-simple-questions">Lesson #26: Yes, No and Simple Questions</a></h3><h3><a href="post/932921652/lesson-27-nasalisations-part-1">Lesson #27: Nasalisations Part 1</a></h3><h3><a href="post/938215810/lesson-28-verbs-part-2-the-present-tense">